# Cloudflare Pages redirects
# https://developers.cloudflare.com/pages/configuration/redirects/
#
# Pages automatically serves /foo.html at /foo and 308-redirects /foo.html -> /foo.
# Canonicals across the site are therefore extensionless; we only need to handle
# trailing-slash variants and legacy aliases here.
#
# Note: apex -> www (funcitygamesnwa.com -> www.funcitygamesnwa.com) cannot be
# configured here — _redirects sources are path-only. Configure that as a
# Cloudflare Redirect Rule at the zone level (dashboard > Rules > Redirect Rules).

# Trailing-slash variants -> canonical extensionless URL
/about/        /about        301
/contact/      /contact      301
/games/        /games        301
/how-it-works/ /how-it-works 301
/locations/    /locations    301
/venues/       /venues       301

# Legacy/convenience aliases
/home /         301

# Direct /404 hits should return a 404 status, not 200. Pages auto-uses
# 404.html as the SPA fallback for actual misses (correct 404 status); this
# rule only handles the case where someone visits the bare /404 URL.
/404           /404.html     404

# Tooling/source files that ship via the Git Integration deploy (.cfignore is
# only honored by `wrangler pages deploy`, not Git pushes). Serve the 404 page
# with a 404 status so internal docs and config files aren't publicly fetchable.
/CLAUDE.md                       /404.html  404
/README.md                       /404.html  404
/Makefile                        /404.html  404
/serve.py                        /404.html  404
/.cfignore                       /404.html  404
/.gitignore                      /404.html  404
/.mcp.json                       /404.html  404
/.playwright-mcp.config.json     /404.html  404
/.playwright-mcp/*               /404.html  404
/.vscode/*                       /404.html  404
/.claude/*                       /404.html  404
/.devcontainer/*                 /404.html  404
/.git/*                          /404.html  404
/images/README.md                /404.html  404
